            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/857.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>sea bass fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sea bass fillet[s]</strong>, skin side down with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, transfer your <strong>sea bass</strong> to the same plate as the wilted pak choi</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/18-06-24_09h18m14s-APIC-1719591415943-x200.jpg",
